  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the drained rice with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span>cold water and a generous pinch of salt to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614700054889-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614700054889-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614700054889-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614700054889-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614700054889-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614700066466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614700066466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614700066466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614700066466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614700066466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, combine your <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>toasted sesame seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> bibimbap sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657786577049-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657786577049-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657786577049-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657786577049-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1657786577049-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and slice<strong> </strong>your<strong> radishes</strong> (as finely as you can)</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into discs, then slice into half moons and slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657786581685-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657786581685-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657786581685-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657786581685-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1657786581685-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated carrot </strong>and <strong>sliced radish </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>remaining rice vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>quick-pickled carrot & radish</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat, once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> spinach </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted, then transfer to a bowl and reserve the pan – this is your <strong>garlic spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657786586825-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657786586825-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657786586825-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657786586825-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1657786586825-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and <strong>courgette</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened and golden</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> soy sauce </strong>and <strong>remaining toasted sesame oil </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Once golden, transfer the <strong>cooked veg</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinated veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657786589554-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657786589554-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657786589554-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657786589554-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1657786589554-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into the pan</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657786592195-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657786592195-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657786592195-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657786592195-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1657786592195-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sticky rice </strong>in a bowl with the <strong>marinated veg</strong>, <strong>garlic spinach </strong>and<strong> quick-pickled carrot & radish </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with a<strong> fried egg </strong>and the<strong> bibimbap sauce </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Tip: To eat this the Korean way, give everything a mix up to coat it all in the bibimbap sauce</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
